This paper deals with properties of linear codes, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and coding theory (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the weight compatible order on the generalized support of a vector, which is related to combinatorics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper discusses test sets and trial sets, which are commonly used in machine learning and optimization (cs.SI).
